{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":861,"text":"Caitlin Quattromani: The election\nof 2016 felt different."},{"time":4578,"text":"Political conversations\nwith our family and friends"},{"time":7625,"text":"uncovered a level of polarization"},{"time":9435,"text":"that many of us had not\npreviously experienced."},{"time":12670,"text":"People who we always thought\nwere reasonable and intelligent"},{"time":16217,"text":"seemed like strangers."},{"time":17826,"text":"We said to ourselves,\n\"How could you think that?"},{"time":20509,"text":"I thought you were smart.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":22405,"text":"Lauran Arledge: Caitlin and I met\nin the summer of 2011,"},{"time":25822,"text":"and we bonded around being working moms"},{"time":27736,"text":"and trying to keep\nour very energetic boys busy."},{"time":30826,"text":"And we soon found out\nwe had almost everything in common."},{"time":34318,"text":"From our love of Colorado\nto our love of sushi,"},{"time":37835,"text":"there wasn't much we didn't agree on."},{"time":40661,"text":"We also discovered that we share\na deep love of this country"},{"time":43678,"text":"and feel a responsibility\nto be politically active."},{"time":47256,"text":"But no one's perfect --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":48931,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":50003,"text":"and I soon found out\ntwo disappointing things about Caitlin."},{"time":54030,"text":"First, she hates camping."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56677,"text":"CQ: I think camping is the worst."}]},{"cues":[{"time":58749,"text":"LA: So there would not be\nany joint camping trips in our future."},{"time":63081,"text":"The second thing is that\nshe's politically active all right --"},{"time":66765,"text":"as a conservative."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68590,"text":"CQ: I may hate camping,\nbut I love politics."},{"time":71916,"text":"I listen to conservative talk radio\njust about every day,"},{"time":75145,"text":"and I've volunteered for a few different\nconservative political campaigns."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79311,"text":"LA: And I'd say I'm a little to the left,"},{"time":81637,"text":"like all the way to the left."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83075,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":84678,"text":"I've always been interested in politics."},{"time":86798,"text":"I was a political science major,"},{"time":88400,"text":"and I worked as a community organizer\nand on a congressional campaign."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92178,"text":"CQ: So as Lauran and I\nwere getting to know each other,"},{"time":94852,"text":"it was right in the middle\nof that 2012 presidential campaign,"},{"time":97799,"text":"and most of our early\npolitical conversations"},{"time":100316,"text":"were really just based\nin jokes and pranks."},{"time":103244,"text":"So as an example, I would change\nLauran's computer screen saver"},{"time":106300,"text":"to a picture of Mitt Romney,"},{"time":107753,"text":"or she would put an Obama\ncampaign magnet on the back of my car."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111174,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":112209,"text":"LA: Car, not minivan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114273,"text":"CQ: But over time,\nthose conversations grew more serious"},{"time":117305,"text":"and really became\na core of our friendship."},{"time":119988,"text":"And somewhere along the line,"},{"time":121430,"text":"we decided we didn't want to have\nany topic be off limits for discussion,"},{"time":125433,"text":"even if those topics pushed us way\noutside of our friendship comfort zone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129911,"text":"LA: And so to most of us,"},{"time":131139,"text":"political conversations\nare a zero-sum game."},{"time":133759,"text":"There's a winner and there's a loser."},{"time":135760,"text":"We go for the attack and we spot\na weakness in someone's argument."},{"time":139037,"text":"And here's the important part:"},{"time":140544,"text":"we tend to take every comment\nor opinion that's expressed"},{"time":143664,"text":"as a personal affront\nto our own values and beliefs."},{"time":147517,"text":"But what if changed the way\nwe think about these conversations?"},{"time":151215,"text":"What if, in these heated moments,"},{"time":153501,"text":"we chose dialogue over debate?"},{"time":156786,"text":"When we engage in dialogue,\nwe flip the script."},{"time":160298,"text":"We replace our ego and our desire to win"},{"time":163099,"text":"with curiosity, empathy"},{"time":165202,"text":"and a desire to learn."},{"time":166711,"text":"Instead of coming\nfrom a place of judgment,"},{"time":168801,"text":"we are genuinely interested\nin the other person's experiences,"},{"time":172697,"text":"their values and their concerns."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175220,"text":"CQ: You make it sound so simple, Lauran."},{"time":177781,"text":"But getting to that place\nof true dialogue is hard,"},{"time":180626,"text":"especially when we're talking\nabout politics."},{"time":183061,"text":"It is so easy to get emotionally fired up"},{"time":185700,"text":"about issues that we're passionate about,"},{"time":187840,"text":"and we can let our ego\nget in the way of truly hearing"},{"time":190799,"text":"the other person's perspective."},{"time":192556,"text":"And in this crazy political climate\nwe're in right now,"},{"time":195153,"text":"unfortunately, we're seeing\nan extreme result"},{"time":197969,"text":"of those heated political conversations,"},{"time":200339,"text":"to the point where people are willing\nto walk away from their relationships."},{"time":204332,"text":"In fact, Rasmussen released\na poll earlier this year"},{"time":207325,"text":"that said 40 percent of people\nreported that the 2016 election"},{"time":212063,"text":"negatively impacted\na personal relationship,"},{"time":215111,"text":"and the Journal of Cognitive\nNeuroscience tells us"},{"time":217571,"text":"that people tend to feel\ntheir way to their beliefs"},{"time":220524,"text":"rather than using reasoning,"},{"time":222261,"text":"and that when reason and emotion collide,"},{"time":225342,"text":"it's emotion that invariably wins."},{"time":227786,"text":"So no wonder it's hard\nto talk about these issues."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230389,"text":"LA: And look, we're just\ntwo regular friends"},{"time":232462,"text":"who happen to think very differently"},{"time":234796,"text":"about politics and the role\nthat government should play in our lives."},{"time":238415,"text":"And I know we were all taught\nnot to talk about politics"},{"time":241075,"text":"because it's not polite,"},{"time":242543,"text":"but we need to be able to talk about it,"},{"time":244480,"text":"because it's important to us\nand it's a part of who we are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":247659,"text":"CQ: We have chosen\nto avoid political debate"},{"time":250445,"text":"and instead engage in dialogue"},{"time":252692,"text":"in order to maintain what we fondly call"},{"time":255257,"text":"our bipartisan friendship."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257058,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":258812,"text":"LA: And this election\nand all of the craziness that has followed"},{"time":261844,"text":"has given us several opportunities\nto practice this skill."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264897,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":266763,"text":"Let's start with January\nand the Women's March."},{"time":268979,"text":"At this point, you can probably guess\nwhich one of us participated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272430,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":273797,"text":"CQ: Oh, the Women's March."},{"time":275790,"text":"I was annoyed and irritated\nthat entire day,"},{"time":278616,"text":"really because of two things."},{"time":280431,"text":"Number one, the name \"Women's March.\""},{"time":283320,"text":"As a conservative woman,"},{"time":284580,"text":"the march's platform of issues\ndidn't represent me,"},{"time":287596,"text":"and that's OK,"},{"time":288794,"text":"but hearing it talked about\nas this demonstration of sisterhood"},{"time":292089,"text":"and solidarity for all women"},{"time":293780,"text":"didn't ring true for me."},{"time":295463,"text":"The other piece\nwas the timing of the event,"},{"time":297536,"text":"the fact that it was the day\nafter the presidential inauguration."},{"time":300868,"text":"It felt like we weren't even\ngiving the new administration"},{"time":303608,"text":"to actually do anything, good or bad,"},{"time":305785,"text":"before people felt the need\nto demonstrate against it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308886,"text":"LA: And under normal circumstances,\nI would agree with Caitlin."},{"time":311864,"text":"I think an administration\ndoes deserve the benefit of the doubt."},{"time":314889,"text":"But in this case, I was marching\nto show my concern"},{"time":318180,"text":"that a man with such a poor track record\nwith women and other groups"},{"time":321673,"text":"had been elected as president."},{"time":323825,"text":"I had to be part of the collective voice"},{"time":325817,"text":"that wanted to send a clear message\nto the new president"},{"time":328783,"text":"that we did not accept or condone"},{"time":331071,"text":"his behavior or rhetoric\nduring the election."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334065,"text":"CQ: So I'm already feeling\nkind of aggravated,"},{"time":336647,"text":"and then I see this Facebook from Lauran\npop up in my social media feed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341084,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":342115,"text":"Seeing Lauran's sons at the march\nand holding signs"},{"time":345456,"text":"took it to a new level for me,\nand not in a good way,"},{"time":348774,"text":"because I know these boys,"},{"time":350394,"text":"I love these boys,"},{"time":351854,"text":"and I didn't feel they were old enough"},{"time":353760,"text":"to understand what the march stood for."},{"time":355696,"text":"I didn't understand\nwhy Lauran would choose"},{"time":357767,"text":"to have them participate in that way,"},{"time":359584,"text":"and I assumed it wasn't a choice\nthat the boys made for themselves."},{"time":362932,"text":"But I also know Lauran."},{"time":365334,"text":"You're an incredible mom"},{"time":366573,"text":"who would never exploit\nyour boys in any way,"},{"time":369132,"text":"so I had to stop and check myself."},{"time":370903,"text":"I had a decision to make."},{"time":372591,"text":"I could take the easy way out"},{"time":374219,"text":"and just choose\nnot to say anything to her,"},{"time":376993,"text":"and instead just kind of simmer\nin my frustration,"},{"time":380034,"text":"or I could ask her to learn more\nabout her motivations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":383265,"text":"LA: And I shared with Caitlin"},{"time":384671,"text":"that we actually started\ntalking about the March"},{"time":387004,"text":"weeks before we participated."},{"time":388674,"text":"And my boys were curious\nas to why the event was being organized,"},{"time":391902,"text":"and this led to some\nvery interesting family conversations."},{"time":395583,"text":"We talked about how in this country,\nwe have the right and the privilege"},{"time":399131,"text":"to demonstrate against\nsomething we don't agree with,"},{"time":401877,"text":"and my husband shared with them\nwhy he thought it was so important"},{"time":405013,"text":"that men joined the Women's March."},{"time":406987,"text":"But the most significant reason\nwe marched as a family"},{"time":409892,"text":"is that it was a way for us to honor\nmy parents' legacy."},{"time":413367,"text":"They spent their careers"},{"time":414864,"text":"working to defend the rights\nof some of our most vulnerable citizens,"},{"time":418772,"text":"and they passed these values\ndown to me and my brother,"},{"time":421369,"text":"and we want to do the same with our sons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423547,"text":"CQ: After talking to Lauran,"},{"time":424910,"text":"I really understood not only\nwhy she felt it was so important to march,"},{"time":428791,"text":"but why she had her boys with her."},{"time":430704,"text":"And frankly, my assumptions were wrong."},{"time":432975,"text":"It was the boys who wanted to march"},{"time":434704,"text":"after they talked about\nthe issues as a family."}]},{"cues":[{"time":437343,"text":"But what's most important\nabout this example"},{"time":439475,"text":"is to think about the alternative."},{"time":441300,"text":"Had Lauran and I not talked about it,"},{"time":443143,"text":"I would have been annoyed with her,"},{"time":444835,"text":"and it could have resulted\nin an undercurrent of disrespect"},{"time":447636,"text":"in our friendship."},{"time":448826,"text":"But by asking Lauran questions,\nit allowed us to use dialogue"},{"time":452004,"text":"to get to a place of true understanding."},{"time":454383,"text":"Now, to be clear,"},{"time":455976,"text":"our conversation didn't really change\nmy mind about how I felt about the March,"},{"time":459865,"text":"but it absolutely changed my thinking\naround why she brought her boys with her."},{"time":464029,"text":"And for both of us,\nthat dialogue allowed us to understand"},{"time":467038,"text":"each other's perspective\nabout the Women's March"},{"time":469331,"text":"even though we disagreed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471315,"text":"LA: The second topic that challenged\nour ability to engage in dialogue"},{"time":474954,"text":"was around my need to understand"},{"time":476991,"text":"how Caitlin could vote for Trump."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479498,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":485483,"text":"Caitlin is a successful professional woman"},{"time":488932,"text":"who is deeply caring and compassionate,"},{"time":491563,"text":"and the Caitlin I know"},{"time":492968,"text":"would never excuse any man\nfrom talking about women"},{"time":496151,"text":"the way that Trump did\nduring the campaign."},{"time":498751,"text":"It was hard for me to reconcile\nthese two things in my mind."},{"time":501834,"text":"How could you overlook\nthe things that were said?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":504937,"text":"CQ: So I'm guessing I may not be\nthe only one here that thought"},{"time":507915,"text":"we didn't have the best choices\nfor the presidential election last year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511321,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":512764,"text":"The Republican candidate who I did support\ndidn't make it out of the primary,"},{"time":516684,"text":"so when it came time to vote,\nI had a decision to make."},{"time":519784,"text":"And you're right,\nthere were some terrible things"},{"time":522095,"text":"that came out during the Trump campaign,"},{"time":524232,"text":"so much so that I almost decided\nto just abstain"},{"time":526779,"text":"rather than voting for president,"},{"time":528388,"text":"something I had never\neven considered doing before."},{"time":531166,"text":"But ultimately,\nI did vote for Donald Trump,"},{"time":533389,"text":"and for me it was really a vote\nfor party over person,"},{"time":536934,"text":"especially recognizing\nhow important that presidential pick is"},{"time":540680,"text":"on influencing our judicial branch."},{"time":543328,"text":"But I shared with Lauran\nit was a decision I really wrestled with,"},{"time":546527,"text":"and not one that I made lightly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":548856,"text":"LA: And so after our conversation,\nI was struck by a few things."},{"time":552287,"text":"First, I had fallen victim\nto my own confirmation bias."},{"time":556026,"text":"Because of my strong feelings about Trump,"},{"time":558398,"text":"I had given all Trump voters\nthe same attributes,"},{"time":561090,"text":"and none of them forgiving."}]},{"cues":[{"time":562678,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":563852,"text":"But knowing Caitlin,\nI started to ask questions."},{"time":568026,"text":"What were Trump voters\nreally concerned about?"},{"time":570540,"text":"Under all the divisive language,\nwhat was really going on?"},{"time":574183,"text":"What could we learn\nabout ourselves and our country"},{"time":576912,"text":"from this unlikely event?"},{"time":579336,"text":"I also learned that we shared\na deep disappointment in this election,"},{"time":583718,"text":"and that we have growing concerns\nabout our two-party political system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587815,"text":"But the most important thing\nabout this conversation"},{"time":590454,"text":"is that it happened at all."},{"time":593074,"text":"Without an open and honest dialogue\nbetween the two of us,"},{"time":596486,"text":"this election would have been\nthe elephant in the room"},{"time":599162,"text":"for the next four years, pun intended."}]},{"cues":[{"time":601851,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":606295,"text":"CQ: So, look --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":607470,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":609756,"text":"So, look -- we know it takes work\nto get past the difficult,"},{"time":613169,"text":"frustrating and sometimes emotional parts"},{"time":615558,"text":"of having discussions about issues\nlike the Women's March"},{"time":618543,"text":"or why your friend may have voted\nfor a candidate that you can't stand."},{"time":623252,"text":"But we need to have these conversations."},{"time":625491,"text":"Our ability to move past political debate"},{"time":628062,"text":"into true dialogue"},{"time":629562,"text":"is a critical skill we should all\nbe focused on right now,"},{"time":632588,"text":"especially with the people\nthat we care about the most."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635904,"text":"LA: And it's not just as adults\nthat we need to bottle this behavior."},{"time":639191,"text":"It's critical that we do it\nfor our children as well."},{"time":642203,"text":"My sons were inundated with this election."},{"time":644897,"text":"We were listening\nto the news in the morning,"},{"time":647065,"text":"and they were having conversations\nwith their friends at school."},{"time":650560,"text":"I was concerned that they were picking up\nso much polarizing misinformation,"},{"time":654704,"text":"and they were growing really fearful\nof a Trump presidency."},{"time":658734,"text":"Then one day, after the election,\nI was taking my sons to school,"},{"time":663259,"text":"and my younger son,\ncompletely out of the blue,"},{"time":665752,"text":"said, \"Mom, we don't know anybody\nwho voted for Trump, right?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":670680,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":673673,"text":"And I paused and I took a deep breath."},{"time":678243,"text":"\"Yes, we do.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":679449,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":680473,"text":"\"The Quattromanis.\""},{"time":681944,"text":"And his response was so great."},{"time":684037,"text":"He kind of got this confused\nlook on his face, and he said ..."},{"time":687719,"text":"\"But we love them.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":688894,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":691886,"text":"And I answered, \"Yes, we do.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":693703,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":694781,"text":"And then he said,\n\"Why would they vote for him?\""},{"time":698412,"text":"And I remember stopping and thinking"},{"time":700152,"text":"that it was really important\nhow I answered this question."},{"time":703589,"text":"Somehow, I had to honor\nour own family values"},{"time":706375,"text":"and show respect for our friends."},{"time":708877,"text":"So I finally said,"},{"time":710473,"text":"\"They think that's the right direction\nfor this country.\""},{"time":713165,"text":"And before I had even gotten\nthe whole sentence out,"},{"time":715983,"text":"he had moved on to the soccer game\nhe was going to play at recess."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719150,"text":"CQ: So life with boys."}]},{"cues":[{"time":720346,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":721403,"text":"So what Lauran and I have discovered\nthrough our bipartisan friendship"},{"time":724787,"text":"is the possibility that lives in dialogue."},{"time":727791,"text":"We have chosen to be genuinely curious"},{"time":730157,"text":"about each other's ideas and perspectives"},{"time":732859,"text":"and to be willing to listen to one another\neven when we disagree."},{"time":736703,"text":"And by putting aside our ego\nand our preconceived ideas,"},{"time":739852,"text":"we've opened ourselves up\nto limitless learning."},{"time":742782,"text":"And perhaps most importantly\nfor our relationship,"},{"time":745608,"text":"we have made the commitment to each other"},{"time":747664,"text":"that our friendship is way more important"},{"time":750553,"text":"than either of us being right\nor winning a conversation about politics."},{"time":755200,"text":"So today, we're asking you\nto have a conversation."},{"time":758405,"text":"Talk to someone outside\nof your political party"},{"time":760696,"text":"who might challenge your thinking."},{"time":762341,"text":"Make an effort to engage with someone"},{"time":764190,"text":"with whom you might typically\navoid a political conversation."},{"time":767183,"text":"But remember, the goal isn't to win,"},{"time":770072,"text":"the goal is to listen and to understand"},{"time":772734,"text":"and to be open to learning something new."}]},{"cues":[{"time":775767,"text":"LA: So let's go back to election night."},{"time":778064,"text":"As the polls were closing"},{"time":779351,"text":"and it became clear that Trump\nwas going to be our new president,"},{"time":782684,"text":"I was devastated."},{"time":784665,"text":"I was sad, I was confused,"},{"time":787320,"text":"and I'll be honest -- I was angry."},{"time":790053,"text":"And then just before midnight,"},{"time":791760,"text":"I received this text message from Caitlin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":794141,"text":"[I know this is a hard night for you guys."},{"time":797537,"text":"We are thinking of you. Love you.]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":800665,"text":"And where there so easy could have been\nweeks or months of awkwardness"},{"time":804499,"text":"and unspoken hostility, there was this --"},{"time":808182,"text":"an offering of empathy\nrooted in friendship."},{"time":811734,"text":"And I knew, in that moment,\nthat we would make it through this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":815692,"text":"CQ: So we must find a way\nto engage in meaningful conversations"},{"time":819332,"text":"that are going to move us\nforward as a nation,"},{"time":821708,"text":"and we can no longer wait"},{"time":823153,"text":"for our elected officials\nto elevate our national discourse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":827069,"text":"LA: The challenges ahead\nare going to require all of us"},{"time":830311,"text":"to participate in a deeper\nand more meaningful way ..."},{"time":833950,"text":"and it starts with each one of us"},{"time":836252,"text":"building connection through dialogue --"},{"time":838435,"text":"in our relationships, our communities"},{"time":842126,"text":"and as a country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":844179,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":845354,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}